<h6>This involves using the mixture of both digit and word in writing numbers.</h6>
<b>Example 1</b>
<br>
Write the following in a mixture of digits and words; 
<br>
(i) 3 200 000. 
<br>
(ii) 5 700 000 000.
<br>
(iii) 140 000 000. 
<br>
(iv) 300 000 000 000.
<br>
<b>Solution</b>
<br>
(i)	3 200 000 = 3.2 x 1 000 000 => <b>3.2 million</b>
<br>
(ii)	5 700 000 000 = 5.7 x 1 000 000 000 => <b>5.7 billion</b>
<br>
(iii)	140 000 000 = 140 x 1 000 000 =><b> 140 million or 0.14 billion</b>
<br>
(iv)	300 000 000 000 = 300 x 1 000 000 000 => <b>300 billion or 0.3 trillion</b>
<br>
<b>Example 2</b>
<br>
Express the following numbers in digits only;
<br>
(i) $2 million.
<br>
(iii) 2.2 million litres.
<br>
<b>Solution</b>
<br>
(i)	$2 million => <b>$2 000 000</b>
<br>
(ii)	2.2 million litres =><b> 2 200 000 litres</b>
</article>


